▁the ▁construction ▁of ▁jur ak udai ▁began ▁in ▁february ▁158 6 ▁, ▁as ▁an ▁office ▁and ▁an ▁official ▁residence ▁of ▁hideyoshi ▁, ▁who ▁became ▁kanpaku ▁( ▁chief ▁advisor ▁to ▁the ▁emperor ▁) ▁, ▁a ▁chief ▁councilor ▁to ▁the ▁emperor ▁, ▁and ▁completed ▁in ▁september ▁158 6 ▁.
